---
description: Require braces on all control flow statements (if, else, for, while)
globs: "**/*.ts"
alwaysApply: false
---

# Braces Required on Control Flow

All `if`, `else`, `for`, and `while` statements must use braces, even for single-line bodies. Braceless inline forms are not allowed.

## Prohibited

```typescript
if (hadSubmitted) inc.submission_count = -1;

if (condition) return;

for (const item of items) doSomething(item);
```

## Required

```typescript
if (hadSubmitted) {
   inc.submission_count = -1;
}

if (condition) {
   return;
}

for (const item of items) {
   doSomething(item);
}
```
